<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f107900241555039>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Necro Cudgels!!</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11"></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Mar 11th 5:53 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=251710><span id= >Rathenecro</span></a><br><span id=notbold>89 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.25]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Er, tzsjynx can I say that you are obviously a person who has minimal knowledge of the uses of necros on a raid.&nbsp;&nbsp;  Or perhaps I should say a high end raid.  Over time necros deal more damage than any other class, including wizards.  A reasonably long fight like Xegony will see a necro deal out a truckload more damage than anyone else if they are actually playing a DPS role and not engaged in constant feeding.  Admittedly this depends on the quality of your clerics, but with dots we outdamage anyone.  <br><br>On most raids necros nuke and nuke hard, using Neurotoxin, disease based DD.  Not many things resist disease, although cold and fire are often resisted, just fyi. We will never outdamage a wizard on DD, BUT other damage classes have many focus items to enhance their damage.  Would I wear the lovely Cloak of Combustion with the Eci 30% on it?  Nope.  Definitely should go to a wizard, dru, shm, or beast.  Cold casters all.<br><br>Would I wield this Cudgel?  Yup you bet.  With Staff of Lost Rituals in secondary I get 20% extra on dots, with this 30% on nukes.  It is situational.  In a short fight I would use this and the Staff, just in case I cast a dot.  In a long fight I would be breaking out my Crystal Rod of Control with Vengeance of Time Focus 25% to dots, and my Affliction Efficiency 4 shield.   A cleric won this today on our POEb warlord clearing, and everyone was glad for her (grats Sympatroniqe).  So,  when she is AE nuking her heart out at Coir she will have an extra kick in her condemnation.  Did I bid against her?  Yes, but do I mind that I didn&amp;#8217;t win?  No.  She had a better claim on it than me at this time, and it is good for any class that can use it.  That&amp;#8217;s why it&amp;#8217;s a non-specialist focus.<br><br>Try seeing things from a necro point of view sometime.  With GoD FOMM3 AA  and ToLM2 I outnuke many of our wizards and mages with disease nukes and magic based lifetaps on certain mobs.  On others they blast mobs to bits that are disease resistant and vulnerable to fire and cold.  So would I be bidding on this with a clear conscience?  Since I don&amp;#8217;t have the mask from RZtW you bet I will be.  If some other class wins it over me because of better ratio or DKP I will be glad for them, as it will improve the overall damage of my guild.  If I win I am quite sure they would be just as happy to see this necro nuking for 3k plus on a regular basis than is currently possible.<br><br><br>Slacthehard Prophet said &amp;#8220;the mobs who drop this is doable by 1 group I've been told.&amp;#8221;  Nope, they lied.   I don&amp;#8217;t think he is one groupable at this stage of the game, though maybe someone from FoH might be able to provide evidence to the contrary.  The minimum I have seen him done with is 24.<br><br><br>Dirty necro and proud of it!<br></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Vermilya<br>70 Deathspeaker<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1189873" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1189873</a></td></tr>
